[There is a nice summary and website references provided in the most
recent reference below. The report of a new virus in swine reminds
us that new syndromes, often manifesting reproductive loss, occur
periodically in swine. A new virus like this can sometimes cause
enormous economic impact, as was the case for PRRS (Porcine
Reproductive and Respiratory Disease), which began to make its global
appearance in the early 1990s. The important question now that we
have identified the emergence of a disease in the Australian swine
population is how far and fast will it spread, if at all. - Mod.PC]
